            <div type="translation" xml:lang="en" resp="#JP">
                <p>Here lies Eutychios who, on account of his faith, has received his place in the lap of Abraham.
                    Having lived 35 years, he died on the 6th day before the Ides of [---]ber.</p>
            </div>
            <div type="translation" xml:lang="it" resp="#SA">
                <p>Qui giace Eutychios che, per la sua fede, ha ricevuto il suo posto nel grembo di Abramo. Dopo aver
                    vissuto 35 anni, morì sei giorni prima delle Idi di [---]ber.</p>
            </div>
            <div type="commentary" xml:lang="en">
                <p>Eutychios is a fairly common name, but rare in Sicily. The text is Christian, as indicated by the
                    phrase enthade kite and the chi-rho symbol at the end, but the initial phrase is strongly Jewish in
                    form. Some have suggested that Eutychios was Jew who converted to Christianity, but it is simpler to
                    see this as a good example of the extensive interaction and influence between the Christian and
                    Jewish communities in ancient Catania.</p>
            </div>
